text: The Shoshone Range is a mountain range in Lander County, Nevada. The northeast end of the range extends into Eureka County at Shoshone Point on the Humboldt River.Crescent Valley, Nevada, 30x60 Minute Quadrangle, USGS, 1987 (40116-A1-TM-100)Battle Mountain, Nevada, 30x60 Minute Quadrangle, USGS, 1988 (40116-E1-TM-100) The range was named from the Shoshoni language meaning "grass". == References == Category:Mountain ranges of Nevada Category:Mountain ranges of Eureka County, Nevada Category:Mountain ranges of Lander County, Nevada Range, Shoshone
